solution.p:
Using the information that the radius of the circle (also the hypotenuse of the right triangle) is 3,
\sin\left(\frac{\theta}{2}\right)&=\frac{\frac{d}{2}}{3}=\frac{d}{6}
Since the question tells us the sector is no more than a quarter of the circle, we know 0 \leq \theta \leq \dfrac{\pi}{2}, so 0 \leq \dfrac{\theta}{2} \leq \dfrac{\pi}{4}. This puts \dfrac{\theta}{2} well within the range of arcsine. \theta&=2\arcsin\left(\frac{d}{6}\right)

